# Package Manager: pnpm

This project uses **pnpm**. Never use `npm`, `yarn`, or `bun` for installs, scripts, or lockfile changes.

## Commands

| Task | Command |
|------|---------|
| Install dependencies | `pnpm install` |
| Add dependency | `pnpm add <pkg>` |
| Add dev dependency | `pnpm add -D <pkg>` |
| Remove dependency | `pnpm remove <pkg>` |
| Run a script | `pnpm run <script>` or `pnpm <script>` |
| Update lockfile | `pnpm install` (after editing `package.json`) |

## Rules

- Use `pnpm-lock.yaml` as the lockfile — do not create or commit `package-lock.json` or `yarn.lock`.
- When adding packages in shell commands or docs, always show the `pnpm` equivalent.
- For monorepo-style filters (if added later): `pnpm --filter <pkg> <command>`.
- Prefer `pnpm exec <bin>` (or `pnpm dlx <pkg>` for one-off CLIs) instead of `npx`.

## Examples

```bash
# ✅ GOOD
pnpm install
pnpm add three
pnpm run dev
pnpm run build

# ❌ BAD
npm install
yarn add three
npx vite build
```
